  "prompt": "If husband donot want havesex for three years. Is nikha still valid?",
  "response": "In Islamic jurisprudence, prolonged sexual abandonment is a serious issue that can potentially affect the validity of a marriage. Here are some key points:\n\n1. According to most Islamic scholars, if a husband deliberately and without valid reason refuses sexual intimacy with his wife for an extended period (like 3-4 months), it could be grounds for:\n- Potential marital discord\n- Wife's right to seek divorce (khula)\n\n2. If the husband has a legitimate reason for abstinence (like medical condition, prolonged travel, etc.), then the marriage remains valid.\n\n3. If there's no valid reason and the husband consistently refuses intimacy, the wife can:\n- Seek counseling\n- Consult Islamic scholars\n- Eventually pursue legal separation if the situation doesn't improve\n\n4. Complete absence of sexual relations for years without valid justification might be considered a form of harm (darar) that could potentially invalidate the marriage contract.\n\n5. Islamic marriage is not just a civil contract but also includes mutual rights and responsibilities.\n\nRecommendation:\n- Communicate openly about the issue\n- Seek marriage counseling\n- Consult a knowledgeable Islamic scholar who can provide specific guidance based on detailed understanding of the specific situation\n\nNote: These are general guidelines, and specific situations require personalized scholarly consultation.",
